article.headline: Texas-Arlington 93, Texas State 84
article.story: ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) -- Ro'ger Guignard scored 19 points and Tommy Moffitt had 17 points and 11 rebounds to lead Texas-Arlington past Texas State 93-84 on Saturday. Texas-Arlingon (13-16, 8-8 Southland Conference) led by 13 early in the second half before Texas State rallied late. Brandon Bush scored 25 points, and Chris Agwumaro and Dylan Moseley each had 12 for Texas State (9-20, 4-12). Agwumaro's basket brought the Bobcats within 85-82 with 1:47 remaining, but Rodrick Epps hit two free throws to stretch the lead to five. Guignard scored the last six points, hitting four straight free throws and adding a basket in the final 49 seconds to put the game away. Anthony Vereen and Larry Posey each chipped in with 15 points for Texas-Arlington.
